<div id="divhow">    <h2>How it works</h2>    <div class="howitworks-div">        <span class="number">1</span>        <div style="width:25%; display: inline-block; padding: 0px 2% 2%; vertical-align:top; text-align:left;">            <p><img src="./img/howitworks/top100.png">            </p>             <p>An Open Knowledge Maps visualization presents you with a topical overview for your search term.            </p>        </div>        <span class="number">2</span>        <div style="width:25%; display: inline-block; padding: 0px 2% 2%; vertical-align:top; text-align:left;">            <p><img src="./img/howitworks/textsimilarity.png">            </p>            <p>We use text similarity to create the knowledge maps.                The algorithm groups those papers together that have many words in common.            </p>        </div>        <span class="number">3</span>        <div style="width:25%; display: inline-block; padding: 0px 2% 2%; vertical-align:top; text-align:left;">            <p><img src="./img/howitworks/headstart-search.png"></p>            <p>The visualization is intended to give you a head start on your                 literature search. You can also use Open Knowledge Maps to stay up-to-date - just limit your search to the most recent papers in the options.            </p>        </div>    </div></div>